.Dd $Mdocdate: December 4 2015 $
.Dt REBOUND 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm rebound
.Nd DNS proxy
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm rebound
.Op Fl d
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
daemon proxies DNS requests.
It listens on localhost and forwards queries to another server.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c Ar config
Specify an alternative configuration file, instead of the default
.Pa /etc/rebound.conf .
At present, the config file consists of a single line containing the next
hop DNS server.
.Nm
will reload the configuration file when sent a SIGHUP signal.
.It Fl d
Debug mode.
.Nm
does not
.Xr fork 2
into the background.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/rebound.confXX" -compact
.It Pa /etc/rebound.conf
Default
.Nm
configuration file.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr resolv.conf 5 ,
.Xr unbound 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
daemon first appeared in
.Ox 5.9 .
